<HL>
   Canadian Government Bond Sale
</HL>
<DATE>
07/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.6
billion Canadian dollars (US$1.38 billion) of bonds in four
issues this week.
   Its sale will involve 11.75% bonds due Oct. 15, 1993;
10.75% bonds due Dec. 15, 1995; 10.50% bonds due July 1,
2000; and 10.25% bonds due March 15, 2014. Offering terms are
to be announced today.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least C$100
million of the new bonds. The remainder will be available to
public investors.
   Proceeds will be used to redeem C$1.53 billion of bonds
maturing Aug. 1 and for general government purposes.
</TEXT>
